ANC veteran Winnie Madikizela-Mandela was admitted to the Milpark Hospital in Johannesburg on Thursday night. Madikizela-Mandela s spokesman Victor Dlamini said she had been admitted for a routine check-up and was kept for additional observation according to reports. In December last year Madikizela-Mandela 80 was rushed to hospital for reasons not made known to the public. This followed her stay in hospital in April of the same year following back surgery. Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share